mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: link function at runtime on Windows
Creates a process in suspended mode (likely to inject code)
System process connects to network (likely due to code injection)
Runs a DLL by calling functions
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
Uses HTTPS for network communication, use the SSL MITM Proxy cookbook for further analysis
Creates files inside the user directory
Monitors certain registry keys / values for changes (often done to protect autostart functionality)
May try to detect the virtual machine to hinder analysis (VM artifact strings found in memory)
Tries to detect sandboxes and other dynamic analysis tools

registry_keys_opened: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\  t I J t I

ids_alerts.rule_raw: alert udp $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET 53 ( msg:"INDICATOR-COMPROMISE suspicious .bazar dns query"; flow:to_server; byte_test:1,!&,0xF8,2; content:"|05|bazar|00|",offset 11,nocase; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop,policy security-ips drop; service:dns; classtype:misc-activity; sid:48680; rev:3; )

ids_alerts.rule_msg: ET HUNTING Observed DNS Query for EmerDNS TLD (.bazar)
